mention.text: the impression that was creeping into me
Atticus strolling around with his hands in his pockets
exactly the same as a cold February morning , when the mockingbirds were still
my children are missing , have n't turned up since noon
Mr. Tate who handed it to the clerk who handed it to the judge
the Judge we did n't hear
better n to take your little sister to that trial
Calpurnia giving her precious Jem down the country -- what new marvels would the evening bring
the middle aisle toward the south exit
the people below us , and from the image of Atticus 's lonely walk down the aisle
a polite thing for little ladies to hear
the only ones whose behavior seemed normal
the officers of the court , the ones present -- Atticus , Mr. Gilmer , Judge Taylor sound asleep , and Bert
fourteen men that could pass for redheads , forty heads varying between brown and black
the idea of asking everyone below to concentrate on setting Tom Robinson free
